						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near the Hoṇḍa.</hi></p>						

						<p>The stone denoting the boundary of the field of <hi rend="bold">Limgappa,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Sūrappa,</hi> states that it was erected in the cyclic year <hi rend="italic">Tāraṇa.</hi> Sūrappa seems to have been the accountant <hi rend="italic">(Sānubhōga)</hi> of <hi rend="bold">ommanakaṭṭi.</hi> The characters belong to the <hi rend="bold">7th century A.D.</hi></p>						

